1780418346862846	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyrRI		item.comment	bn-25db	{"body":"Dogfood friction (2026-06-02, via notes/consolidated-sim.sh on 1.0.0-pre.2):\n1. AGENTS.md still documents the v2 BARE layout (ws/default/, bare .git at root) but greenfield 'maw init' and this repo are now consolidated (.maw/workspaces/, normal .git). Every fresh agent reads stale layout docs. Fix in SG5 docs pass (bn-3ctu).\n2. 'maw init --help' says 'greenfield defaults to consolidated' but a brownfield/existing-repo init silently produces v2 BARE; consolidated for an existing repo requires 'maw migrate'. Defensible behavior, but the help wording misleads existing-repo users. Clarify in same docs pass.\n3. NEW durable regression harness: notes/consolidated-sim.sh — 33 invariant checks across greenfield/lifecycle/recover/migrate/post-migrate-merge, incl. the bn-3bkn git-gutting guard. Green on 1.0.0-pre.2 (1 soft warn = bn-sdv4)."}	blake3:pfK1OIDzrCaJOoQiMIRSJWyxHcRi7FkZe7kjjk1ubyc
1780418944487393	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyrhI		item.create	bn-3ej6	{"description":"Found during 2026-06-02 dogfood sim (logged on bn-25db). Two doc-drift\nitems to fix together:\n\n1. AGENTS.md documents the v2 BARE layout throughout — \"Architecture:\n   Bare repo model\", the directory-structure diagram (ws/default/, .git/\n   core.bare=true, repo root metadata-only), and \"Directory Structure\n   (maw v2)\". But greenfield `maw init` and this repo are now the\n   CONSOLIDATED layout: root is a normal checkout with a normal .git/,\n   agents live under .maw/workspaces/<name>/, metadata under .maw/manifold/.\n   Every fresh agent reads stale layout docs. Update the Architecture\n   section, the directory diagram, and any ws/default/ path references to\n   reflect consolidated. Keep v2 mentions only where genuinely needed\n   (e.g. \"legacy v2 via --legacy-ws / migrate from v2\").\n\n2. `maw init --help` says \"Greenfield init defaults to the consolidated\n   .maw/ layout\" — but a BROWNFIELD init on an existing git repo silently\n   produces v2 BARE (verified). Consolidated for an existing repo requires\n   `maw migrate`. The behavior is defensible (don't silently restructure\n   someone's repo), but the help wording misleads existing-repo users.\n   Clarify the help text: state explicitly that brownfield/existing-repo\n   init produces the v2 layout and to use `maw migrate` for consolidated.\n\nScope: docs + help-text strings only, no behavior change. Verify\n`maw init --help` reads correctly and `just check` stays green.\n","kind":"task","labels":["layout","v1-0","docs"],"size":"s","title":"docs: AGENTS.md + init --help still describe v2 bare layout, not consolidated"}	blake3:7i3iQC58SJYFCMpPVXhnFKjVaSLtzVSpFo4xK8aNoss
