1780419148343586	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEysxI		item.create	bn-16x2	{"description":"Found 2026-06-02 dogfooding pre.2 (while staging agent workspaces to fix\nbn-sdv4/bn-3ej6). DISTINCT from the merge-gate false-positive lineage\n(bn-3oau, bn-1i3t, bn-m6ad — all done): those fixed `maw ws merge`'s\nrefusal. This is the STATUS/LIFECYCLE/RESOLVE path, which still scans\ntracked-file content for marker lines and mislabels workspaces.\n\nMINIMAL REPRO (no rebase, no siblings):\n  maw init   (greenfield consolidated, in empty dir)\n  # commit one file whose content legitimately contains marker examples:\n  #   <<<<<<< ours / ======= / >>>>>>> theirs   (a git tutorial, a diff\n  #   doc, a merge tool's own source, a test fixture)\n  maw epoch sync\n  maw ws create solo --from main\nResult on the BRAND-NEW workspace:\n  - maw ws list:  \"solo ... (conflicted: 1 — resolve before merge) [lifecycle:conflicted]\"\n  - \"solo has 1 unresolved REBASE conflict(s)\"   <-- no rebase ever ran\n  - maw ws resolve solo --list  lists the doc file and offers\n      maw ws resolve solo --keep ours|theirs|both   <-- would MANGLE a\n      legitimate file\n  - BUT  maw ws merge solo --into default --check  ->  \"[OK] Ready to merge\"\n    The status detector and the merge gate DISAGREE.\n\nIMPACT\n- Hits the maw repo ITSELF: crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/resolve.rs (79\n  marker-pattern lines in fixtures/doc) and tests/merge_gate_sidecar.rs\n  contain marker literals, so EVERY agent workspace in maw is born\n  \"conflicted: N — resolve before merge\". Verified on bn-sdv4 + bn-3ej6.\n- Any project containing git tutorials, diff docs, merge-tool code, or\n  conflict test fixtures is affected.\n- Directly triggers the dogfood watch-item failure modes: an agent reads\n  \"conflicted: 1 — resolve before merge\", runs `maw ws resolve --keep`, and\n  silently corrupts a non-conflicted file (perceived-loss -> destructive\n  redo). The \"rebase conflict(s)\" wording is actively false.\n\nLIKELY FIX\nThe lifecycle/status conflict signal must come from the structured\nrebase-conflict SIDECAR (.maw/manifold/artifacts/ws/<name>/rebase-conflicts.json\n— empty for these workspaces), NOT from re-scanning tracked-file content.\n`maw ws list`, `maw ws status`, lifecycle:conflicted, and `maw ws resolve\n--list` should all key off \"did a rebase actually record a conflict for\nthis workspace\", matching what merge --check already does correctly. Add a\nregression test with a marker-literal fixture committed to the repo.\n","kind":"bug","labels":["layout","v1-0","conflicts"],"size":"m","title":"ws list/status/resolve report fresh workspaces as conflicted from marker-like file CONTENT (gate fixed in bn-3oau/1i3t/m6ad, status path regressed)","urgency":"urgent"}	blake3:LWF9SY9jnpih_YWimDqS3spTQA9_vXpVMVWgy-bT1uk
