1780422945087428	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyvhI		item.create	bn-lm3i	{"description":"bn-16x2 routed resolve through recorded_conflict_count (sidecar-only) and bails when 0. But dirty-default merge-overlap conflicts write conflict markers into default's WORKING COPY with NO sidecar. So 'maw ws resolve default --keep <path>=both' now errors 'no recorded rebase conflicts'. Caught by tests/action_workflow_dst.rs::dst_action_sequences_preserve_contracts (was masked earlier by a stale target/debug/maw binary — cargo clippy in 'just check' updates the fingerprint so cargo test skips relinking the bin, and maw_bin() execs the stale one). The distinction bn-16x2 missed: COMMITTED marker literals (clean tree) = false positive; DIRTY working-copy markers (from merge overlap) = genuine. Fix: resolve must still handle dirty working-copy marker conflicts when no sidecar exists, without reintroducing the committed-marker false positive.","kind":"bug","labels":["conflicts","v1-0"],"size":"s","title":"bn-16x2 regression: maw ws resolve bails on dirty-default content conflicts (no sidecar)","urgency":"urgent"}	blake3:BbuOyv81A8TzBXTorVaMSL6EeGvssvmpdce7bFZ7dNk
