1780431429889845	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEywxI		item.create	bn-8nm6	{"description":"just check runs 'fmt-check clippy test ...'. The integration tests (tests/*.rs via manifold_common::maw_bin()) exec target/<profile>/maw, but cargo test does NOT reliably relink that binary: cargo clippy runs first and updates cargo's fingerprint for maw-cli, so the subsequent cargo test treats the bin as fresh and skips producing it. Tests then run against a STALE target/debug/maw from a previous build.\n\nIMPACT: a real behavior regression can pass 'just check' GREEN and only surface later. Confirmed 2026-06-02: the bn-16x2 merge introduced a 'maw ws resolve' regression (bn-lm3i) that 'just check' reported green because cargo test ran against the pre-bn-16x2 binary; it only failed once the binary was explicitly rebuilt with 'cargo build -p maw-cli'. This undermines 'just check' as a reliable gate for any maw-cli behavior change.\n\nFIX OPTIONS: (a) make the 'test' recipe depend on building the binary, e.g. 'cargo build -p maw-cli' before 'cargo test' (or a 'build-bin' prerequisite on the check/test recipes); (b) have manifold_common::maw_bin() build the binary on demand (e.g. via escargot or a std::process cargo build) and/or use a CARGO_BIN_EXE_* path from a crate that actually produces the maw bin so cargo's dep graph forces a relink; (c) run clippy AFTER test in the check sequence. Prefer (a) — cheapest and deterministic. Add a note in maw_bin() about the gotcha.","kind":"bug","labels":["ci","tooling"],"size":"s","title":"just check can mask integration-test regressions (stale target/debug/maw via clippy fingerprint)"}	blake3:ptrlSRGXwhY1rZH-3eeTRj_eCVpnDv4WbB3fm0i7kEk
