1781090532267006	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy0hI		item.comment	bn-1abp	{"body":"Worker started: setting up workspace bn-1abp to fix (1) silent sibling rewrite notification, (2) stale-warning dedupe, (3) UX minors (sync --rebase deprecation docs, ws diff vs epoch, exec-outside-repo error, create --from epoch override)."}	blake3:7HAUewYMarmkqyI06CC-408lnfD41na-mBQ_ufQXqFY
1781090951325646	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy0xI		item.comment	bn-36zz	{"body":"Implemented in workspace bn-36zz (commit 5382af0e): render_content_conflict now does a hunk-level gix diff3 merge for the 2-side case (labels unchanged: 'epoch (current)' / 'base' / '<ws> (workspace changes)'), header gains '# base blob:' + '# side <ws> blob:' OID lines for mechanical reconstruction, tripwire first line + atoms lines kept, whole-file render kept as fallback for N>2 sides and clean-merge edge (gate/sidecar consistency). 3 new unit tests; 21/21 materialize tests green; full 'just check' running."}	blake3:qKos519zAmgxNTLeBj0fVoX2zxl6T5s7khCcPV-8VwY
1781092223920200	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy1BI		item.comment	bn-1abp	{"body":"Progress: all fixes implemented in ws bn-1abp — (1) auto-rebase notice JSON in .manifold artifacts + one-time print on next maw exec + AGENTS.md template doc (--no-auto-rebase already existed); (2) stale-warning latch: at most one WARNING block per maw process; (3a) user-facing strings no longer recommend flagged 'ws sync --rebase'; (3b) ws diff default baseline changed default-ws-state-ref -> epoch (matches tldr docs; fixes sibling-work misattribution) + explicit empty-diff one-liner; (3c) outside-repo error now explains cd-to-repo; (3d) verified --from IS honored; added loud NOTE when --from diverges from epoch. Tests added in auto_rebase_siblings/sync/diff. Running just check."}	blake3:ZntsV-gj1ilDd0takravOahI2hSILLAXVxEqv1evNEw
1781092347234190	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy1RI		item.comment	bn-1abp	{"body":"DONE in ws bn-1abp, commit fd64689b. just check fully green (exit 0, 56 suites, 0 failures). (1) notice JSON at <manifold>/artifacts/ws/<name>/auto-rebase-notice.json written by sibling auto-rebase for all Rebased* outcomes; one-time NOTE printed+consumed by next maw exec (and ws sync); --no-auto-rebase already existed — documented in generated AGENTS.md template. (2) root cause of repeats: one warning per maw process, but every exec in the remediation sequence re-warns; added process-local latch (at most once per invocation) + integration guard. (3a) all maw-owned strings now use unflagged 'maw ws sync'. (3b) ws diff default baseline -> epoch (was default-ws state ref — misattributed sibling merges); empty diff now says what was compared. (3c) outside-repo error explains cd-to-repo fix. (3d) --from IS honored; loud NOTE added when it diverges from epoch. NOT merged — awaiting review."}	blake3:BxIqtU06AeWEEtfrc8mvYqpqAMC0ej7PzYV88PXYHV0
1781092842718573	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy1hI		item.comment	bn-21cj	{"body":"DONE (workspace bn-8zqz, commit 7e1e8bc5, not merged). Root cause confirmed: the rebase summary keyed only off THIS replay run's ConflictTree, so replaying a marker-laden commit (from a quiet sibling auto-rebase) onto a newer epoch printed 'replayed cleanly' AND the 'clean run' branch deleted the legacy sidecar while placeholder blobs sat in HEAD. Fix: after a no-new-conflicts replay, rebase.rs inspects the FINAL HEAD via the new shared workspace::conflict_state helper (sidecar verified against marker evidence + bn-28d1 placeholder-blob tripwire). If residual conflict content is present: no 'cleanly', sidecar preserved (both flavors), conflicted-branch guidance printed, RebaseOutcome.conflicts reflects it — summary now always matches resolve --list. Truly clean runs clear BOTH sidecars (old code cleared legacy only). Tests: tests/conflict_state_truth.rs::sync_replaying_committed_conflict_does_not_claim_cleanly (+4 more). just check green."}	blake3:az5zOotsDQhaeCSh4uF_iUuo_KeWmw5fGRUbS0ZrmBo
1781092853950093	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy1xI		item.comment	bn-8zqz	{"body":"DONE (workspace bn-8zqz, commit 7e1e8bc5, not merged). One source of truth: new crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/conflict_state.rs — effective_conflict_state() verifies the structured/legacy sidecars against reality (marker evidence on recorded paths via find_conflicted_files_filtered + bn-28d1 placeholder blobs in HEAD). Stale sidecar (manual resolution committed, zero evidence) = RESOLVED and auto-cleared by the FIRST reader with the one-line 'Cleared stale conflict metadata...' notice — no follow-up ws sync needed; the !is_stale guard in sync no longer blocks clearing. No-sidecar-but-placeholder-blobs = UNRESOLVED (gate still refuses, --force still can't bypass; resolve --list now lists those paths too). Wired into: merge gate (merge + --check), ws conflicts (was: unfiltered marker scan — bn-16x2-class false positives gone), resolve --list, and lifecycle conflicted via effective_recorded_conflict_count (ws list, ws status, maw status, ws diff, destroy preview). bn-lm3i dirty-working-copy fallback untouched; committed marker literals stay invisible. Tests: tests/conflict_state_truth.rs (5 tests incl. reader-order independence + stale-workspace clearing); merge_rebase_reconcile's ws_conflicts embedded-marker test updated to assert gate agreement. just check green."}	blake3:1qAQEUOGREyS3TGh_k3_kaVWCYQTRj_7ZHTk6k-R82A
1781093016583233	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy2BI		item.comment	bn-36zz	{"body":"DONE in workspace bn-36zz, commit 5382af0e (not merged/pushed). render_content_conflict now emits hunk-level gix diff3 merges for the 2-side case: non-overlapping edits merge cleanly into the body, only genuine overlaps get minimal marker hunks with the exact legacy labels ('epoch (current)' / 'base' / '<ws> (workspace changes)'). Header keeps the bn-28d1 tripwire first line + atoms lines and adds '# base blob: <oid>' / '# side <ws> blob: <oid>' for mechanical reconstruction (git cat-file + git merge-file). Whole-file render kept as fallback for N>2 sides and the clean-merge edge (keeps <<<<<<< gate consistent with the sidecar). Compat verified: structured resolve --keep materializes from sidecar OIDs (untouched); legacy marker-scan resolver already handles multi-block files; find_conflicted_files scans line-start <<<<<<<. just check green: EXIT=0, 56 suites, ~1867 tests, 0 failures. 3 new unit tests incl. the different-regions+one-overlap proof."}	blake3:PBp4jsooYbX-YkInZFgQ_yX1VQP2Lt-8zn8Ipkt6pwY
1781093390956347	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy2RI		item.comment	bn-36zz	{"body":"Merged to main feb7b2dc: render_content_conflict now does hunk-level gix diff3 (2-side fast path), whole-file fallback for N>2/clean-driver edge; blob OIDs in header for mechanical reconstruction. Combined just check green."}	blake3:lFhEqOOv_3xI53_eGNL3BDbnhxnWHK6U0u1tdObleqk
