1781102309422037	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy9hI		item.create	bn-1hmz	{"description":"Found banging on the conflict pipeline in a /tmp repo (debug build post-7c40c398).\nTwo unguarded merge_text call sites treat binary blobs as text:\n\n(1) HIGH: `try_clean_three_way_overlap` (crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/sync/rebase.rs\n~1589) — during sync/auto-rebase replay, a binary file edited by both the epoch and\nthe workspace in DIFFERENT byte regions (binary content often contains 0x0A, so the\ntext driver sees \"lines\") gets a CLEAN 3-way text merge that fabricates bytes\nNEITHER side ever had, committed silently as \"rebased clean\". Demonstrated:\nbase 'HDR\\x00aaaa\\nMID\\x00bbbb\\nEND\\x00cccc\\n'; epoch changed HDR line, ws changed\nEND line -> replay produced HDR\\x00XXXX + END\\x00ZZZZ frankenstein, no conflict\nrecorded. For real binaries (images, executables, archives) this is silent\ncorruption-by-merge; git itself refuses to text-merge binaries (git merge-file:\n\"cannot merge binary files\"). The bn-2upt post-merge sanity check does not catch\nit (size-plausible, .bin not AST-parsed). The binary-SAFE rendering in materialize\n(bn-ad5z) only engages when the merge CONFLICTS — the clean path has no guard.\nFix: in try_clean_three_way_overlap, if any of base/epoch/ws blobs fails\nlooks_text (NUL byte / invalid UTF-8 — same heuristic as materialize.rs), return\nOk(None) so the path routes through the conflict tree and the binary-conflict\nstub. A binary file changed on both sides is ALWAYS a conflict (pick a side).\n\n(2) MEDIUM: `--keep <ws>` (bn-3mbj Theirs path, crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/\nresolve_structured.rs ~783-836) runs merge_text/merge_text_with_style with NO\nlooks_text guard — unlike the --keep epoch (Ours) and --keep both (Union) paths\nright above it, which bn-1nwn guarded. A binary conflict resolved with --keep <ws>\nwhere the epoch made disjoint binary edits gets a frankenstein result; the output\nline also claims \"(3-way merge: ws intent on top of epoch...)\" for binary files.\nFix: add the same looks_text guard, falling back to whole-blob replace (which IS\ncorrect for binary --keep).\n","kind":"bug","title":"Binary blobs run through gix TEXT 3-way merge without guard — rebase fabricates 'clean' binary merges; resolve --keep <ws> same gap"}	blake3:_OXXPRiYhI8O8gZ1pHmvHTpPQ6OKjEf83ZH7IjWoNro
1781102309644643	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy9xI		item.create	bn-39i8	{"description":"Found banging on the bn-28d1 tripwire in a /tmp repo (debug build post-7c40c398).\nSetup: genuine conflict committed by auto-rebase, then the sidecar files deleted\n(simulating tamper/loss). The merge gate correctly blocks (even --force — good),\nand resolve --list / --keep correctly refuse. But the guidance is a dead loop:\n- `maw ws resolve u --list` says: \"To fix: regenerate the metadata with\n  `maw ws sync --rebase u`, or restore each file's real content and commit.\"\n- `maw ws sync u` (the workspace is at the current epoch) prints \"up to date,\n  but has 1 unresolved conflict(s): ... Resolve: maw ws resolve u --list\" and\n  does NOT regenerate anything (nothing replays on an up-to-date workspace; the\n  sidecar stays missing). Round and round.\nThe only working exit is the second suggestion (hand-edit the placeholder file,\ncommit). Three fixes:\n1. The suggested command uses the DEPRECATED flagged form `maw ws sync --rebase`\n   that bn-1abp purged elsewhere (these strings were added concurrently by the\n   bn-8zqz worker — grep resolve.rs/resolve_structured.rs for \"--rebase\").\n2. Don't suggest sync at all unless it would actually do something; for an\n   up-to-date workspace it cannot regenerate the sidecar.\n3. The real fix: since bn-36zz the placeholder blob HEADER embeds everything\n   needed for mechanical reconstruction (`# base blob: <oid>`, `# side <ws>\n   blob: <oid>`). `maw ws resolve` could parse those OIDs from the placeholder\n   blob and either rebuild the sidecar or resolve --keep directly from them\n   (verify the blobs exist via cat-file first). Alternatively fall back to the\n   legacy per-marker-block resolution (resolve.rs parse_file_conflicts) which\n   can already resolve the marker structure without a sidecar.\n","kind":"bug","title":"Placeholder-blob-without-sidecar state has circular recovery guidance; suggested sync does not regenerate the sidecar"}	blake3:pSwdHJOSKy3-3HeYfTyuSrBstnwmPiODclB7xdkaIxk
1781102309866156	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy-BI		item.create	bn-566k	{"description":"Found banging on modify/delete conflicts in a /tmp repo (debug build post-7c40c398).\nAsymmetry in the rebase/replay overlap handling:\n- epoch MODIFIES + workspace DELETES -> correctly raised as a structured\n  [modify_delete] conflict with an excellent rendered stub (\"# modify/delete\n  conflict at <path>\", modifier/deleter OIDs, epoch content inline). GOOD.\n- epoch DELETES (another workspace's merged deletion) + workspace MODIFIES the\n  same file -> auto-rebase replays \"rebased clean (1 commit(s))\", the file\n  survives in the workspace, and the subsequent merge silently RESURRECTS the\n  deleted file on main. No conflict, no warning, anywhere in the flow.\nRepro: ws v deletes big.txt, ws w modifies line 2; merge v (w auto-rebases\n\"clean\", big.txt still present in w); merge w -> big.txt is back on main.\nv's explicit, merged intent (deletion) is silently reverted — the same \"silent\noverwrite\" class the epoch-delta injection (bn-7phd) exists to prevent, just for\nthe delete direction. Likely cause: the overlap promotion pre-pass\n(promote_overlaps_to_conflicts, sync/rebase.rs) considers Add/Modify entries in\nthe workspace patch against epoch-changed paths, but an epoch-side DELETE doesn't\ninstall a conflict against a workspace-side MODIFY. Expected: surface a\n[modify_delete] (or delete_modify) structured conflict in this direction too —\nthe machinery and rendering already exist; sides reversed (deleter: epoch,\nmodifier: <ws>).\n","kind":"bug","title":"Epoch-deleted vs workspace-modified file silently resurrects on merge (asymmetric modify/delete handling)"}	blake3:peQmSvFMG7tW-RHLBgkFjIuGT37oHDY33cdkpPbGudQ
1781102451350185	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy-RI		item.move	bn-1hmz	{"state":"doing"}	blake3:2f_eJU8iCOrt7p3WmRmwchSj2MtZaKp0waE9NTdoJhg
