1781102689535540	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEygRM		item.comment	bn-1hmz	{"body":"Starting fix. Plan: (1) make looks_text pub in maw-core/src/merge/materialize.rs so it can be reused from maw-cli; (2) use it in try_clean_three_way_overlap (rebase.rs) to return Ok(None) on binary input; (3) use it in the --keep <ws> Theirs path (resolve_structured.rs) to fall back to blob-replace; (4) update resolve_structured.rs to import from maw_core instead of local copy; (5) add integration tests for both sites."}	blake3:9dZnszwBvhC7Ao6DeKM15YsvhFriAimZo4fwIu1bfKo
1781103855491578	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyghM		item.comment	bn-566k	{"body":"Fix complete. Commit bdcee8b8 in ws bn-566k.\n\nThe hole: promote_overlaps_to_conflicts in sync/rebase.rs line 1204 had `None => continue` when epoch delta showed a deletion (ref_new == None) while workspace had an Add/Modify. Workspace content sailed through clean → merger silently resurrected deleted file on main.\n\nFix: replaced the bare `continue` with a ModifyDelete conflict install (modifier=ws, deleter=epoch). Resolution flows work correctly: --keep epoch → Ok(None) → file stays deleted; --keep <ws> → Ok(Some(blob)) → file kept with ws content; --keep both → bn-2pry alias → keeps modifier (ws). The existing ws-deletes/epoch-modifies direction is untouched.\n\nDelete+re-add edge case: also conflicted (same shape, same rationale — silent resurrection must not happen).\n\nTests: 3 new tests in sync_rebase_semantics.rs — exact repro (bn566k_epoch_delete_vs_ws_modify_produces_modify_delete_conflict), re-add edge case (bn566k_epoch_delete_vs_ws_add_produces_conflict), regression guard for existing direction (bn566k_ws_delete_vs_epoch_modify_still_conflicts). All 3 pass; just check fully green (0 failures)."}	blake3:4gY3QSRjX5WN1g6HJrOZwcqJ1jp3DYt7xpglBhPoAmE
1781104186259455	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEygxM		item.comment	bn-39i8	{"body":"Done: implemented placeholder header reconstruction in resolve.rs (bc1eb28d). try_reconstruct_sidecar_from_placeholders() parses all 4 header formats (text/binary/modify-delete/add-add), verifies every OID against the object store, and writes a valid ConflictTree sidecar. resolve --list now reconstructs and dispatches to the structured path on success; on parse failure (corrupted/stripped headers) it falls back to graceful-refusal with correct guidance (no --rebase, no sync suggestion). Added 4 integration tests in conflict_state_truth.rs. just check fully green (35/35 conflict_state_truth, all test suites pass)."}	blake3:lqzJdR7-B0nhQBcfT_haW6eqNzNRlNGUAZ4X0yvW_zM
1781104272760020	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyhBM		item.comment	bn-1hmz	{"body":"Fix complete — commit af734df9. All just check green.\n\nChanges:\n- maw-core/src/merge/materialize.rs: looks_text promoted fn → pub #[must_use]\n- crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/sync/rebase.rs: import looks_text from maw-core; binary guard added at line ~1600 (after reading 3 blobs, before merge_text call) — returns Ok(None) on any binary blob\n- crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/resolve_structured.rs: removed local looks_text copy; import from maw-core; binary guard added in --keep <ws> Theirs path (~line 787) — falls through to BlobReplace on any binary blob\n- tests/manifold_common/mod.rs: add read_file_bytes, add_file_bytes, modify_file_bytes, seed_binary_files helpers\n- tests/sync_rebase_semantics.rs: sync_rebase_binary_blob_not_clean_merged — epoch/ws edit disjoint regions of binary blob; asserts conflict-tree.json present, no frankenstein mix\n- resolve_structured.rs unit: resolve_keep_ws_binary_falls_back_to_blob_replace — --keep <ws> writes ws bytes wholesale, not mixed\n\nGuard locations:\n- Site 1 (HIGH, rebase): crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/sync/rebase.rs around line 1600 (in try_clean_three_way_overlap)\n- Site 2 (MEDIUM, resolve): crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/resolve_structured.rs around line 787 (in --keep <ws> Theirs path)\n- Shared looks_text: maw-core/src/merge/materialize.rs line ~314"}	blake3:Qi5S5_g5PTJuGHaA1GPc-vk_Pn-Zy57MZimW3M8gkkU
1781104995471259	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyhRM		item.create	bn-c5ui	{"description":"Found dogfooding the real bn-1hmz + bn-566k merge (both appended test blocks to\ntests/sync_rebase_semantics.rs; the sibling rebase produced a structured conflict).\n`maw ws resolve <ws> --keep both` (gix Union) split the overlapping hunk across a\nstatement boundary — the resolved file lost the tail of one side's block mid-\n`assert!(...)` (unclosed delimiter, rustc error) — and resolve then AUTO-COMMITTED\nthe broken file and reported success: \"resolved: ... (kept both sides in conflicted\nhunk(s); preserved cleanly-merged changes from both sides)\" / \"Workspace is ready\nfor merge.\" The merge gate agreed and the broken file reached main.\nUnion-on-code being syntax-unaware is inherent diff3 behavior (git merge-file\n--union has the same hazard) — the bug is that maw already HAS a defense it didn't\nuse: the bn-2upt post-merge sanity check (run_post_merge_sanity in sync/rebase.rs)\ndoes size-ratio + AST-parse plausibility checks on rebase merges. Resolution\noutputs (--keep both especially, but any per-hunk resolution) should run the same\ncheck before auto-commit and, on failure, either skip the auto-commit and warn\nloudly (\"resolved file fails to parse; review before committing: <path>\") or\nappend a WARNING line to the success output. Do not block the resolution itself —\nthe user may be resolving non-code files; just never SILENTLY commit output that\nthe sanity checker can tell is implausible.\nRepro shape: two sides append different multi-line blocks at EOF of a .rs file ->\nstructured conflict -> resolve --keep both -> output interleaves the blocks at the\ncommon-suffix boundary -> rustc unclosed-delimiter error; resolve reported success.\n","kind":"bug","title":"resolve --keep both/side auto-commits syntactically broken output without running the bn-2upt sanity check"}	blake3:sNKVSIoK-8Mr-M1S5VLLt0OEN2bN6fedSTQRwWUb_ao
1781104995567047	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyhhM		item.comment	bn-1hmz	{"body":"Merged 4adbd8d5: looks_text now pub in maw-core materialize; guards in try_clean_three_way_overlap (binary -> conflict-tree path -> binary stub) and resolve_structured keep-ws Theirs path (binary -> blob-replace). Tests prove no frankenstein bytes. Combined just check green."}	blake3:TEzlFXekgAHdhjEwDBCeL1-3GtxupS_48GKL8Fjmhpc
