1781106709218438	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEylhM		item.comment	bn-heb8	{"body":"DONE — commit 93a338d6 in workspace bn-heb8. just check fully green (all tests pass, fmt+clippy clean). Rename detection via exact blob-match in detect_epoch_rename_target(); rename_hint threaded as Option<PathBuf> field on Conflict::ModifyDelete with serde(default) for backward compat. Stub includes '# note: deleted by rename — content now lives at <new-path>'. --keep epoch always prints discarded-blob note (OID + git cat-file hint). resolve --list appends '(renamed to <path>)'. 5 new tests covering sidecar hint, list suffix, discard note (both rename+plain), no false positives, old-sidecar backward compat."}	blake3:-FWdldmpxHnFFya3V97p3Ru2kn_OnC2TTRbbjC0ujds
1781107074949221	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEylxM		item.comment	bn-ztu6	{"body":"Fix complete (c0406696). Changed recover_diff3_atoms to recover_diff3_atoms_with_participants — re-runs the k-way fold tracking which workspace IDs are party to the first conflicting pairwise step. resolve_shared_path now filters entries to those participants before building the Diff3Conflict record. All 4 new tests pass, just check 100% green."}	blake3:v4TGFxHDswyJm9EDu7rVkZnnVi25mVk9PVhG6oOk1nY
1781107296992751	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEymBM		item.comment	bn-c5ui	{"body":"Fix complete (commit c55168a5). Extracted shared sanity module to sync/sanity.rs with PostMergeSanityConfig + SanityFailure + run_post_merge_sanity. Wired into resolve_structured.rs on ThreeWayClean/ThreeWayWsWins/ThreeWayEpochWins/ThreeWayUnion paths before auto-commit. Union disables size check (size_ratio_max=INFINITY), AST check still guards it. On failure: file written, auto-commit suppressed, WARNING + manual git commands printed. JSON adds sanity_warnings field. Tests: c5ui_sanity_failure_skips_autocommit_and_writes_file, c5ui_clean_union_still_autocommits, c5ui_non_rs_txt_union_no_sanity_warning. just check green (0 failures)."}	blake3:4TGDSBBwI0KjSFNSGNOgH3P_gOQIKUnGy70lRmqnI3E
1781108219121049	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEymRM		item.comment	bn-ztu6	{"body":"Round-2 fix (3ff739f5): review found order-dependence — disjoint workspace sorting FIRST folded cleanly into ours and was still attributed. Root causes: (1) participant set was 'all folded members + trigger'; (2) round-1 fix only patched resolve_shared_path while the production CLI uses resolve_shared_path_with_ast (ast-merge default feature). Fix: pairwise exclusion probe — folded member is a participant only if diff3(base, member_content, trigger_content) conflicts; applied to both resolve paths; atom ours-labels rebuilt from participants. E2E verified with rebuilt binary: a-disjoint/z1/z2 --check now reports [z1, z2]; m1/m2/zz-disjoint still [m1, m2]. New tests: bn_ztu6_disjoint_source_sorted_first_excluded_from_sides + bn_ztu6_ast_path_disjoint_sorted_first_excluded_from_sides. just check green."}	blake3:uBCfXHqkgekb0kFNugfygSnng6pc4bWAg3WtYLjZNDw
