1781109755933480	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEynRM		item.comment	bn-1mn0	{"body":"DONE: fix committed in workspace bn-1mn0 at cf18a44b.\n\nPart 1 (resolve.rs): try_reconstruct_sidecar_from_placeholders now calls ConflictSide::with_base(ws_name, oid, dummy_ordering(), base_oid.clone()) instead of ConflictSide::new(), threading the parsed base OID into each text-conflict side.\n\nPart 2 (resolve_structured.rs): Added effective_base_oid<'a>(conflict_base, side) helper that prefers side.base_content and falls back to Conflict::Content.base. Updated all three per-hunk keep paths:\n- --keep epoch: uses effective_base_oid(conflict_base, epoch_side)\n- --keep <ws>: uses effective_base_oid(conflict_base, ws_side) for both the 3-way guard AND the legacy-warn guard (replaces ws_side.base_content.is_none())\n- --keep both: uses effective_base_oid(conflict_base, epoch_side) (was reading Conflict::Content.base directly — now goes through the helper)\n\nPart 3 (fallback warnings): Added no-base-available eprintln! for --keep epoch (fires when 2-sided text Content conflict has no base anywhere) and --keep both (same condition before legacy concat). Both match the wording of the existing --keep <ws> warning.\n\nTests (conflict_state_truth.rs): 4 new tests:\n- reconstruction_keep_epoch_preserves_disjoint_edit: KEY TEST — overlap+disjoint setup, sidecar deleted, --keep epoch preserves FROM_B_DISJOINT (line 9) and uses epoch's FROM_A (line 4), output contains 'kept epoch in conflicted hunk(s)...' suffix\n- reconstruction_keep_ws_preserves_epoch_disjoint_edit: --keep b after reconstruction, per-hunk suffix present\n- reconstruction_keep_both_uses_per_hunk_union: --keep both after reconstruction, ThreeWayUnion suffix, both FROM_A + FROM_B + FROM_B_DISJOINT present\n- keep_epoch_no_base_emits_warning: add/add conflict (no base), warning on stderr\n\njust check: all green (39 conflict_state_truth tests pass, full suite green)"}	blake3:7Hv26ZABwprlbSuV5FEmO4M2fxfU3ZjGaBSdZOTO8Dc
