1781110279066414	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyphM		item.create	bn-2dy1	{"description":"HIGH. Found in /tmp bang round 4 (debug build post-832725d2). When a path is a\nFILE on one side and a DIRECTORY (prefix of deeper paths) on the other, maw\nsilently drops one side with no conflict, in both pipelines:\n\nDirection 1 — ws file vs epoch dir (rebase replay): ws db commits FILE `deep`\n(\"deep is a file here\"); epoch gains `deep/a/b/c/d/leaf.txt` via merged sibling.\nAuto-rebase reports \"rebased clean\"; db's replayed commit (diff vs parent:\n\"deep/a/b/c/d/leaf.txt | 1 +\") contains NO trace of db's file (git grep exit 1);\n`maw ws diff db` is EMPTY. The original commit survives only as a dangling\nreflog entry (HEAD@{0}) — `maw ws recover --search` finds 0 hits (recovery\nsnapshots only cover destroys). An agent would conclude their work vanished.\n\nDirection 2 — ws dir vs epoch file (rebase replay + MERGE ENGINE): ws fb commits\n`clash/sub.txt`; epoch gains FILE `clash` via merged sibling fa. Auto-rebase\n\"rebased clean\" keeps fb's dir and silently drops the epoch's file from fb's\ntree; then `maw ws merge fb --into default --check` says [OK] and the merge\nDELETES main's `clash` file (fa's merged work) — silent loss of already-merged\ncontent on the default branch, past the --check gate.\n\nExpected: a D/F path clash is a structured conflict (same family as\nmodify_delete — e.g. a FileDirectory conflict or modify_delete-shaped record at\nthe file path, with the dir side represented by its tree OID), surfaced by the\nreplay (workspace conflicted, merge gate blocks) and detected by the merge\nengine's --check. Likely root causes to investigate: (a)\npromote_overlaps_to_conflicts matches exact paths only — a ws Add/Modify at\n`deep` never matches epoch-delta entries at `deep/a/...` (prefix clash) and vice\nversa; (b) tree building in apply/materialize (maw-core merge/apply.rs,\nbuild.rs, write_blobs_and_build_tree) inserts blob-vs-tree at the same name with\nlast-writer-wins instead of erroring; (c) the merge engine's partition/resolve\ntreats `clash` and `clash/sub.txt` as unrelated paths. Fix should cover BOTH\npipelines + tests for both directions; verify the conflict stub/resolution flow\n(--keep epoch / --keep <ws>) makes sense for D/F (keep file vs keep tree).\n","kind":"bug","title":"File-vs-directory path clash silently DROPS a side in rebase replay AND merge engine (Prime Invariant violation, both directions)"}	blake3:bOrZMrMfpScrw-c6OkTkm6sAsLXqJOgYjp6WgWDs2jQ
1781110279313431	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEypxM		item.create	bn-2qbk	{"description":"Cosmetic, from /tmp bang round 4. When resolve suppresses auto-commit after a\nsanity failure (bn-c5ui), the manual remediation prints:\n  maw exec ub -- git add --\n    app.rs\n  maw exec ub -- git commit -m \"resolve: apply --keep decisions for 1 path(s) in 'ub'\"\nThe `git add -- <paths>` command wraps the path list onto following indented\nlines, so copy-pasting the first line stages nothing (and `git add --` alone\nerrors). Per the output guidelines (AGENTS.md: copy-pasteable commands), join\nthe paths onto one line: `maw exec <ws> -- git add -- app.rs ...` (shell-quote\npaths with spaces), or emit one `git add` line per path. In\ncrates/maw-cli/src/workspace/resolve_structured.rs (bn-c5ui suppression block).\n","kind":"bug","title":"Sanity-suppression message renders git add command across two lines — not copy-pasteable"}	blake3:Fi71yD0ndhZdtlivL42vmlVM77Jivaz0fZpjp7sDOKo
