1781110752202809	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyrhM		item.comment	bn-2qbk	{"body":"Done. Fixed the sanity-suppression block in resolve_structured.rs: paths are now space-joined onto the same line as the git add command (or one command per path if joined form exceeds 200 chars). Paths with spaces/metacharacters are single-quoted. No tests needed updating — the bn-c5ui tests only assert HEAD/file-content outcomes, not stderr text. just check: all tests green. Commit: 6dc04cf4."}	blake3:0P-sFbXbjpLO2rrYTXUQ4kmoQM-hk_6lShXseSDUm8Y
1781112589399610	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyrxM		item.comment	bn-2dy1	{"body":"DONE: bn-2dy1 fixed — D/F path clash no longer silently drops sides. Three-layer fix committed (d7ed8638) in workspace bn-2dy1.\n\nLayer A (rebase pipeline): promote_overlaps_to_conflicts now scans epoch_delta for component-wise prefix relationships and emits Conflict::ModifyDelete for each D/F clash (both directions: ws FILE vs epoch dir, and ws dir vs epoch FILE).\n\nLayer B (rebase defense-in-depth): write_blobs_and_build_tree errors out if a D/F clash somehow reaches the output tree rather than silently producing a corrupted git tree.\n\nLayer C (merge engine): partition_by_path records D/F clashes in a new DfClash struct / PartitionResult::df_clashes field. resolve_partition_with_attrs emits ConflictReason::FileDirectory conflicts for all participating paths and skips normal resolution for them — neither side is applied silently.\n\nFalse positive prevention: the prefix check is component-wise (uses P + '/' prefix) so 'deep' vs 'deeper' and 'deep.txt' vs 'deep/sub.txt' are not flagged.\n\nTests: partition unit tests (D/F directions + false-positive cases), resolve unit tests (FileDirectory conflict emission, no silent application of dir-child), integration tests in sync_rebase_semantics.rs for both directions + clean cases. just check passes green."}	blake3:xDC7pNgYl3BtbSxOZJB0NXiivPJLGxJI7DX3-4Rt6g0
1781115397725555	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEysBM		item.comment	bn-2dy1	{"body":"ROUND 2 DONE (lead review response): live auto-rebase D/F wedge fixed — commit 8ef21f67 in workspace bn-2dy1, just check green (exit 0).\n\nROOT CAUSE of the review finding: layer-A promotion DID fire, but produced a structurally invalid output — the conflict stub at collision root P coexisted with the other side's entries (epoch children under P/, or epoch FILE P) in the materialized tree. A git tree cannot hold a path as both file and directory, so my own layer-B backstop aborted the rebase BEFORE the sidecar was written → wedged workspace, no conflict to resolve. Second bug: write_blobs_and_build_tree's removal pass emitted Remove(base_path) for a base FILE that became a DIRECTORY, deleting the just-upserted direction-2 stub subtree (then the stale-metadata auto-clear erased the sidecar). Third: partition-level D/F detection counted Deleted entries as occupying paths, false-positiving the ws's own FILE<->DIR restructure at merge time after --keep <ws>.\n\nFIX: tree-validity invariant — exactly one side's paths in the materialized tree (the ws side, as marker stubs; the epoch side removed but restorable from the immutable epoch commit). New ModifyDelete.df_hint field marks the collision root. resolve --keep epoch now deletes the ws path(s) and RESTORES the epoch's version of the region from the epoch tree (file or whole subtree). D/F-claimed changes dropped from the patch so apply's V1 collapse can't undo the conflict. Removal pass skips file->directory replacements. Deletions excluded from partition D/F detection.\n\nLIVE VERIFIED against the workspace binary (sibling auto-rebase shape from the review): D1 (deep vs deep/a/leaf.txt) and D2 (clash vs clash/sub.txt) both rebase WITH structured conflict ('rebased with 1 conflict(s)'), resolve --list shows the modify_delete with D/F label, merge gate blocks, --keep epoch restores the epoch side, --keep <ws> lands the ws side in main, false positives (deep.txt vs deep/, deep vs deeper) rebase clean. Backstop unreachable in all repros.\n\nTests: auto_rebase_df_clash_direction{1,2}_* (surface/keep-epoch/keep-ws, 6 tests, live shape), sync_rebase_df_clash_direction1_explicit_sync, tightened FP tests, partition deletions-don't-occupy unit test. Flaky test concurrent_different_name_creates_all_succeed_in_parallel re-run 3x standalone: 3/3 pass (pre-existing git index-lock race under parallel load, from bn-3bbc era, untouched by this change)."}	blake3:IdBYpVja2FD_nBE8SliZJ1wBlGxYWOKe8IhN5vO46OI
1781115744658198	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEysRM		item.comment	bn-2dy1	{"body":"Merged: 3-layer D/F fix. Layer A: promote_overlaps_to_conflicts detects component-wise prefix clashes (incl. Add-vs-Add — round-2 fix after lead review caught the live backstop-only behavior), installs ModifyDelete with df_hint, keeps materialized tree valid (one side's paths only). Layer B: removal-pass fix + backstop retained, unreachable in repros. Layer C: partition DfClash + FileDirectory conflict reason in merge engine (deletions excluded). --keep epoch restores epoch region from epoch tree; --keep ws explicit dir/file-wins. Live-verified both directions + FP. Root just check green."}	blake3:P6xtAB_JjBVQIvFigVuMpRofjvXcvSbtFCZ0iqJmvfE
