1781115919542443	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEytRM		item.create	bn-1s8d	{"description":"Found in /tmp bang round 5 (debug build post-a364129f). In a consolidated-layout\nrepo, plain `maw ws clean` (default scope = the default workspace) fails:\n  Error: Workspace 'default' does not exist\n    Check: maw ws list\n    Fix: maw ws create 'default'\nTwo problems: (1) the command resolves the default workspace by looking it up in\nthe workspaces dir — in consolidated layout the default workspace IS the repo\nroot (bn-1lj2/bn-2h3g class: layout-awareness; use LayoutFlavor /\nthe same default-workspace resolution other commands use). `maw ws clean` should\nclean the root's target/ in consolidated. (2) the generic \"Fix: maw ws create\n'default'\" hint is actively harmful — following it creates the bn-<sibling>\nreserved-name zombie (see companion bone). Also `--all` should include the\ndefault/root context in consolidated.\n","kind":"bug","title":"maw ws clean is not layout-aware: errors 'Workspace default does not exist' in consolidated repos and suggests the harmful fix 'maw ws create default'"}	blake3:cc2_yiUCVbD7cIlL5Ds9PHtqg26RLn_C-Rnvr9waSd8
1781115919797676	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEythM		item.create	bn-21qy	{"description":"Found in /tmp bang round 5 (debug build post-a364129f). In a consolidated repo:\n`maw ws create --from main default` SUCCEEDS, creating .maw/workspaces/default —\nan impostor shadowing the reserved default-workspace name. Resulting state:\n- `maw exec default -- pwd` routes to the repo ROOT (special-case wins), so the\n  impostor is unreachable via exec\n- `maw ws merge default --into default --check` refuses (\"Cannot merge the\n  default workspace\") — also name-special-cased\n- `maw ws destroy default --force` REFUSES (\"Cannot destroy the default\n  workspace\") — the impostor is a ZOMBIE: cannot be used, merged, or destroyed;\n  it permanently occupies a git worktree registration and a directory\n- `maw ws list` shows it as a normal workspace (no lifecycle tag), confusing\nFixes: (1) `maw ws create` must refuse the name 'default' (and any other\nreserved names — check names.rs for an existing reserved list; v2-bare was\nprotected by ws/default already existing, consolidated is not). Clear error:\n\"'default' is reserved for the default workspace (the repo root)\". (2) Provide a\ncleanup path for repos that already have the zombie: destroy should allow\nremoving .maw/workspaces/default when the layout is consolidated (where the REAL\ndefault is the root) — guard carefully: only when the path is under the\nworkspaces dir, never the root itself. (3) Fix error hints that suggest creating\nit: the create-requires-source error renders \"maw ws create --from main default\"\nwhen invoked as `maw ws create default`, and ws clean's \"Fix: maw ws create\n'default'\" (companion bone covers clean's root cause).\nTests: create-refusal in consolidated AND v2 layouts; zombie cleanup; hint text.\n","kind":"bug","title":"maw ws create allows reserved name 'default' in consolidated layout -> undestroyable zombie workspace; error hints suggest it"}	blake3:wOF_Ot56gH7MdhKohgU2aPpi9SKfR4sm_Rek-ti8NPU
