1781301012709561	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEywxM		item.create	bn-29z8	{"description":"HIGH (Prime-Invariant adjacent). Field incident in ~/src/sigil (maw 1.0.0-pre.4),\nbone bn-3d4a: worker committed a41e87e1bb0 (parent e2a7158, 2026-06-11T21:27:39Z,\n\"fix: print full anyhow error-cause chains...\", 2 files +247/-65). The commit was\nORPHANED: by 21:38:36Z the workspace HEAD was back at e2a7158 (proof: the lead's\nmanual re-commit 95f10ba2f80e has parent e2a7158), work present on disk\nuncommitted, error_chain.rs untracked, NO replayed twin anywhere in the object\nstore (checked all 1429 unreachable commits), no failure surfaced to anyone. The\nonly maw activity in the window was the bn-h5fq merge (21:33:09-17Z) and the\nworker's own parallel `maw exec bn-3d4a -- git ...` invocations (agents batch\nparallel tool calls). Work was recovered only because the lead noticed at merge\ntime. `maw ws recover --search` finds nothing (no destroy happened); git's own\nsafety warning was swallowed (below). An agent following AGENTS.md exactly can\nlose a committed SHA with zero diagnostics.\n\nCONFIRMED DEFECTS (root-cause audit, current main):\n\nA. crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/sync/checks.rs sync_worktree_to_epoch_inner:\n   runs `git checkout --detach <epoch>` via Command::output() and IGNORES stderr\n   on success. When the worktree HEAD is detached at unmerged commits (every maw\n   workspace is detached), git prints \"Warning: you are leaving N commit(s)\n   behind: <sha> ...\" and SUCCEEDS — maw discards the warning and the commits\n   are silently abandoned. ANY fast-forward over unnoticed commits is silent.\n   Fix: always capture stderr; if it contains the leaving-behind warning,\n   surface it loudly (and ideally refuse + instruct, since the decision to\n   fast-forward was made on stale data — see B).\n\nB. TOCTOU, no lock: auto_sync_if_stale (sync/mod.rs ~427-540, the `maw exec`\n   pre-hook for every git command) does is_stale -> committed_ahead (reads HEAD)\n   -> cross-target -> dirty -> sync_worktree_to_epoch, with NO workspace lock\n   and NO re-verification. The ahead check runs BEFORE the dirty check, so a\n   `git commit` landing between them yields ahead=0 (old HEAD) then clean (new\n   HEAD) and the fast-forward abandons the fresh commit. Same shape in the `maw\n   ws sync` CLI path (mod.rs ~155-215) between its checks and the checkout. The\n   sibling auto-rebase (auto_rebase.rs) DOES take the per-workspace lock and\n   re-reads status under it — exec auto-sync takes no lock at all, yet runs\n   concurrently with worker git processes BY DESIGN (parallel tool calls).\n   Fix: take the same per-workspace lock in auto_sync_if_stale (try-lock; on\n   contention just skip the auto-sync — running the user's command against a\n   stale ws is fine); re-check ahead + capture expected HEAD under the lock\n   immediately before the checkout; make the checkout conditional on HEAD still\n   being the expected OID (compare-and-swap semantics — re-read HEAD right\n   before `git checkout` and abort the sync, not the user's command, if moved).\n   Use the existing failpoint infra (maw::fp!, e.g. FP between ahead-check and\n   checkout) to write a deterministic interleave test: commit lands at the\n   failpoint -> sync must abort, commit must survive.\n\nC. Consider whether exec's auto-sync should mutate at all: silently moving HEAD\n   as a side-effect of `maw exec <ws> -- git status` is the bn-1abp \"mutate\n   under the agent\" class. At minimum, after A+B it must be loud and race-safe.\n   If the team prefers, demote exec auto-sync to a notice (\"workspace is stale;\n   run maw ws sync\") and never mutate from the exec pre-hook — state the choice\n   in the fix.\n","kind":"bug","title":"Silent commit abandonment class: swallowed 'leaving commits behind' + lock-free check-then-act in exec auto-sync / sync fast-forward (sigil bn-3d4a incident)"}	blake3:5i7jyH3gUnmjnQh3sDD8u2rhtWxP8lmATIG08IbaXkg
1781301012971760	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyxBM		item.create	bn-1qtj	{"description":"Companion to the sigil bn-3d4a incident audit. sync_worktree_to_epoch_inner\n(checks.rs ~156-172) updates refs/manifold/epoch/ws/<name> after the checkout\nwith tracing::warn-and-continue on failure (bn-3pkx). A failed/raced write\nleaves the workspace permanently stale-by-ref while HEAD is already at the\nepoch. Consequences observed/derived:\n- every `maw exec <ws> -- git <cmd>` prints the stale warning forever (the\n  sigil worker reported exactly this), because is_stale keys off the ref;\n- committed_ahead_of_epoch(ws, base_ref) then counts EPOCH commits as\n  \"committed work ahead\" (base_ref..HEAD includes the epoch advance), so\n  auto-sync refuses with \"has N committed commit(s) not yet merged\" for\n  commits that are not workspace work at all;\n- a manual `maw ws sync` in that state computes the replay range from the stale\n  base ref and would re-replay epoch commits onto themselves (untested path).\nFixes: (1) make the epoch-ref write failure LOUD (stderr warning with the exact\nref and a fix command), and retry once; (2) self-heal on read: wherever\nis_stale/base_epoch is consulted (lifecycle/status/auto-sync/sync), if the\nworkspace HEAD already equals (or descends from) the current epoch while the\nref lags, fix the ref on the spot and treat the workspace as current —\nmirroring the bn-8zqz auto-clear pattern; (3) test: simulate the desync (write\nan old OID into the ref) and assert warnings stop, ahead-counts exclude epoch\ncommits, and sync becomes a no-op after self-heal.\n","kind":"bug","title":"Workspace epoch-ref desync is permanent and noisy: failed ref write is warn-and-continue; stale-by-ref + HEAD-already-synced never self-heals"}	blake3:OpH6oKLO5pfMF5PX-Ttzam9tOOhQnkddGH9eShYftoo
1781301024755649	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyxRM		item.move	bn-29z8	{"state":"doing"}	blake3:z0Kf_QcywgDOJYiaoosFgZVU0FtV7uWClfTW2DQuU3Y
