1781301071741004	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyyRM		item.comment	bn-29z8	{"body":"Starting work on bn-29z8: reading source files and planning the fix for all three defects (A: swallowed git warning, B: lock-free TOCTOU, C: exec mutate design)."}	blake3:he8lmn-lUP2mkeBP1pZzNI1AZymcE0WlbhzXOs0cmnM
1781301087582911	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyyhM		item.comment	bn-1qtj	{"body":"Starting work on bn-1qtj: epoch-ref desync loud write failure + self-heal. Workspace bn-1qtj created at /home/bob/src/maw/.maw/workspaces/bn-1qtj/. Will implement: (1) retry + loud stderr warning on epoch-ref write failure, (2) self-heal on read when HEAD already at/past epoch, (3) ahead-count correctness doc comment, (4) tests for all three paths."}	blake3:uE9GM1BdbcvO_YqZ-fCHA4bhkWp610iYSOAcUJ_W2LI
1781302564689653	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyyxM		item.comment	bn-1qtj	{"body":"Done. Implemented all three fixes + 4 integration tests. Commit 4be34a20 in workspace bn-1qtj.\n\nSelf-heal predicate (both list() and status()): ALL three must hold — (a) recorded epoch ref is an ancestor of current epoch [ref lags], (b) HEAD is at or past current epoch [workspace already synced], (c) ref != current [something to repair]. The ancestor guard (a) is the critical gate that prevents the heal from corrupting legitimate 'workspace baseline ahead of global epoch' refs (branch-attached workspaces).\n\nWired in: GitWorktreeBackend::list() and ::status() in crates/maw-core/src/backend/git.rs.\n\nFailure-path text (stderr): 'WARNING: failed to update epoch ref for workspace <name> (retried once): <error>' followed by the ref name, OID, and 'Manual fix: git -C <root> update-ref <ref> <oid>'.\n\nTests (tests/epoch_ref_desync.rs):\n- epoch_ref_desync_self_heals_when_head_already_at_current_epoch: desync simulated, no stale warning, ref repaired, sync up-to-date\n- epoch_ref_desync_self_heals_when_head_descends_from_current_epoch: HEAD has ws commits past current epoch, still self-heals\n- genuine_stale_with_workspace_commit_stays_stale_and_warns: genuine stale+ahead case unchanged — stays stale, warning fires, HEAD not moved\n- sync_epoch_ref_write_failure_emits_loud_warning_with_fix_command: read-only ref dir triggers retry+eprintln WARNING on stderr\n\nAll tests pass: just check fully green (all test suites, 0 failures)."}	blake3:Pgco1oc7oa7L_zChpnxvlQ7rcTIhndwos8oNAlqfQPk
1781302958215468	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyzBM		item.comment	bn-2yzz	{"body":"ACCRUAL MECHANISM SWITCHED to a local systemd-timer cron (2026-06-12; commit 61b868f4).\n\nFINDING: the GitHub Actions cron (.github/workflows/dst-soak.yml) was effectively dead — on ubuntu-latest it hit the 180-min job timeout EVERY night, was cancelled, the upload step was skipped ('No files were found'), and it accrued ZERO op-steps. Weeks of nightly runs = no progress (and burned free Actions minutes, now exhausted). Root causes: no internal nightly wall cap (the 100k-seed budget needs ~38h, can't finish in 180min) + no persistent cumulative ledger + GH-hosted single-thread ~30-46 op-steps/sec can't reach 1e8 on a sane calendar (~7 months) anyway. Disabled it (disabled_manually + schedule commented in-repo).\n\nREPLACEMENT: local campaign under scripts/sg1-soak/ — frozen-pinned RELEASE sg1_dst binary (pinned at HEAD d8542518), disjoint-seed slots (SLOT_SEEDS=500 x STEPS=64), nice -19 + ionice idle so it yields to the box's rust compiles, flock-bounded concurrency, append-only JSONL ledger summing clean op-steps toward 1e8, halts on any Oracle A/B violation. Driven by a templated systemd USER timer (sg1-soak@.timer; concurrency = enabled @N instances; runs without login via existing linger). Currently PARALLEL=2 (~18-day calendar at measured ~30 op-steps/sec/core, longer when compiles contend).\n\nMEASURED: ~30 op-steps/sec/core (release==debug; the soak is I/O-bound on git/worktree ops, not CPU). Op-steps/sec does NOT improve with release build; only more cores help.\n\nOPERATE: scripts/sg1-soak/status.sh (cumulative N, Wilson 95% UB, ETA); journalctl --user -u 'sg1-soak@*'. At DONE (1e8, 0 violations) fill notes/sg1-soak-campaign.md 7.1/8 from ~/.local/state/maw-sg1-soak/ledger.jsonl. A violation => STOP flag + violations/*.log = a Prime-Invariant finding (shrink->fix->reset->restart)."}	blake3:A9MyKIJqriewJ5mrSRnQ9T611OZ9AZeFj0-Cn0ou_bg
1781303848563861	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyzRM		item.comment	bn-29z8	{"body":"DONE — commit b89b0ad7 in ws/bn-29z8.\n\nThree defects fixed:\n\nA. Ancestor-refusal: sync_worktree_to_epoch_inner now checks that a detached-HEAD workspace's HEAD is an ancestor-or-equal of the target epoch before issuing git checkout --detach. If HEAD has diverged commits (not in epoch's history), it refuses loudly with named SHAs and a remediation hint. Branch-tracking workspaces (change-branch) are excluded — their branch ref prevents orphaning so the refusal is not needed. Added GitRepo::head_is_detached() + GixRepo impl.\n\nB. Lock+CAS guard in auto_sync_if_stale: acquires the per-workspace rebase lock before the ahead-check, captures HEAD OID under the lock, passes it as expected_head_hex into sync_worktree_to_epoch. Concurrent commit between decision and checkout: CAS detects moved HEAD, skips sync, commit preserved. Lock contention: try-lock only, skips with notice.\n\nC. auto_sync_if_stale prints what it does on every mutation path.\n\nAlso: FP_AUTO_SYNC_BEFORE_CHECKOUT failpoint added; unit tests in checks.rs; integration tests in tests/sync_auto_toctou_bn_29z8.rs (ancestor-refusal, CAS skip, lock-skip, regression guard). just check green (EXIT: 0). DST seed 6840346603195203591 verified clean."}	blake3:8DDJ8s7hLYGyi1Ut79BXAi5D2OABK1kzTHNizxXSRfM
1781310333092169	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyzhM		item.create	bn-20sa	{"description":"HIGH follow-up to bn-29z8, from a SECOND live occurrence of the orphaned-commit\nincident — this time in the maw repo itself, fully forensically captured:\n- ws bn-1qtj committed 4be34a20 at 18:15:53 (parent d8542518; reflog records it).\n- 18:22:11-49: a concurrent agent merged bn-2yzz (61b868f4) + direct bones\n  commits + epoch sync (fb6fde82) and likely ran a post-sync sync/--all.\n- Result: ws HEAD file = fb6fde82 with NO reflog entry, NO replayed twin\n  anywhere (fsck-verified), worktree files left at 4be34a20's content\n  (uncommitted), new test file untracked. Identical signature to the sigil\n  bn-3d4a incident. The dirty sibling (bn-29z8's ws, committed 18:37) was\n  skipped and survived — the bug specifically hits siblings that committed.\nEstablished mechanism constraints: the only HEAD writer that leaves no reflog\nand no worktree mutation is maw-git set_head (checkout_impl.rs ~579, direct\natomic HEAD-file write), called from rebase_workspace_run (sync/rebase.rs ~759)\nafter the replay loop — meaning a rebase ran against epoch fb6fde82 with an\nEMPTY-or-fully-skipped commit list for a workspace that was 1 commit ahead,\nand set_head(new_epoch) abandoned the commit. bn-29z8's merged guards cover\nsync_worktree_to_epoch (checkout path) and exec auto-sync (lock+CAS) but NOT\nthis set_head site.\nFIXES:\n1. Guard rebase.rs set_head with the same never-abandon invariant: capture the\n   workspace HEAD at rebase start; immediately before set_head, re-read it —\n   refuse (loud error naming SHAs) if (a) HEAD moved since the walk (CAS), or\n   (b) the old HEAD is not an ancestor of the new chain AND its exclusive\n   commits were not consumed by this run's replay (replayed-count/commit-set\n   accounting). A 0-replay rebase whose old HEAD carries exclusive commits\n   must NEVER set_head.\n2. Root-cause the empty walk: instrument/walk through how commits are\n   enumerated (walk_commits(base..HEAD)) and how HEAD/base are resolved when a\n   CONCURRENT agent runs the rebase (different process, root cwd) while the\n   workspace owner's processes (cargo/git) run in the worktree. Candidates:\n   gix HEAD resolution under concurrent index/lock activity; base ref\n   force-advanced by a prior refs-only skip; walk error swallowed to empty.\n   Add a deterministic regression test for whatever is found; if unprovable,\n   the (1) guard still makes it loud — say so.\n3. set_head must leave a forensic trail: append a reflog entry for the\n   worktree HEAD (git's files-backend format is simple; or shell out to\n   `git update-ref` with reflog enabled) so future incidents are traceable.\n4. Oplog observability: sibling auto-rebase and sync operations should append\n   to the workspace oplog (`maw ws history` showed only [create] for a ws\n   that had been rebased/ff'd multiple times by other agents' merges).\nReference forensics: orphans 4be34a20 (+ worker intermediates f350b967,\nedc63d0b) in this repo; sigil twins a41e87e/95f10ba in ~/src/sigil.\n","kind":"bug","title":"rebase set_head can still silently abandon commits (live bn-1qtj incident); set_head bypasses reflog; sibling rebases invisible in oplog"}	blake3:Y4fvo5fI2JbAs9PZSocLMjilzlpmcRDjL6I66qTV6Mk
1781310524228118	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyzxM		item.comment	bn-29z8	{"body":"Merged a6499e89: ancestor-refusal before checkout --detach (detached-HEAD ws only, names abandoned SHAs), git stderr surfaced, per-ws lock + expected-HEAD CAS in exec auto-sync, FP_AUTO_SYNC_BEFORE_CHECKOUT failpoint + tests. Live-verified: stale+clean ff works, committed work warned+skipped. NOTE: the rebase.rs:759 set_head path is NOT covered — follow-up bn-20sa (a SECOND live incident hit it during this very fix cycle)."}	blake3:4mjEWgK35ESaZ9o3H-tbMMjBSnKM01YLTiqmUMjOfMA
