1781372363625788	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy2RM		item.create	bn-8flz	{"description":"HIGH, Prime-Invariant violation. Found while auditing whether the orphaned-commit\nclass (sigil bn-3d4a; maw bn-29z8/bn-1qtj/bn-20sa) was fully closed. It was NOT:\n`maw ws advance` is a fourth HEAD-mover that none of those fixes touched, and it\nsilently orphans COMMITTED work while printing \"advanced ... successfully.\"\n\nDETERMINISTIC REPRO (maw 1.0.0-pre.4 debug binary, /tmp):\n  maw init; commit base; epoch sync\n  maw ws create pers2 --from main --persistent\n  # worker commits in the persistent ws:\n  echo \"worker work\" >> .maw/workspaces/pers2/f.txt\n  git -C .maw/workspaces/pers2 commit -am \"WORKER COMMIT\"   # HEAD=45e48324\n  # epoch advances via an unrelated direct commit + epoch sync\n  maw ws advance pers2\nRESULT: prints \"Workspace 'pers2' advanced ... successfully\" with NO warning;\nws HEAD = new epoch (1ed6b05); the worker commit 45e48324 is NOT an ancestor of\nHEAD (orphaned); \"worker work\" is GONE from f.txt on disk. Recoverable only via\nthe dangling object (git reflog DOES have an entry here — advance goes through\n`git checkout` which writes reflog, unlike set_head — so it's less forensically\nblind than bn-3d4a, but the work still silently vanishes from the tree and the\ncommand claims success).\n\nROOT CAUSE: crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/advance.rs. The flow is:\n  1. snapshot_working_copy (stash create) — captures UNCOMMITTED changes only\n  2. checkout_to(ws_path, new_epoch, None) — moves HEAD to the new epoch\n  3. replay_snapshot — restores the UNCOMMITTED snapshot\nCommitted commits ahead of the old epoch are never detected, never rebased, and\nare not in the working-copy stash, so step 2 orphans them. The module doc\n(advance.rs:1-4) CLAIMS it \"rebase[s] a persistent workspace onto the latest\nepoch\" / \"rebases [the workspace's commits]\" — it does not; it only rebases the\nworking copy. There is NO committed_ahead_of_epoch check, NO ancestor guard, NO\nCAS — unlike sync_worktree_to_epoch (bn-29z8) and rebase set_head (bn-20sa).\n\nFIX: advance must handle committed-ahead work the way `maw ws sync` does —\ndetect commits in old_epoch..HEAD and REPLAY them onto the new epoch\n(rebase_workspace_run is the existing machinery; advance is literally the\npersistent-workspace sync, so it should share the replay path), preserving the\nbn-20sa never-abandon guard + reflog/oplog. At minimum (if full replay is out of\nscope), REFUSE loudly when committed-ahead work exists (\"workspace has N\ncommitted commit(s) not in the epoch; advance would orphan them — merge or sync\nfirst\"), never checkout over them, and never print \"successfully.\" Add a\nregression test mirroring the repro: persistent ws + committed-ahead commit +\nadvance → commit survives (reachable from HEAD) and the line is on disk.\n\nSYSTEMIC NOTE (worth a follow-up): the orphan class has now appeared on FOUR\nindependent HEAD-moving paths (sync checkout, exec auto-sync, rebase set_head,\nadvance checkout_to) and was fixed per-path each time. The audit that found THIS\none (grep for every set_head + `git checkout`/`--detach`/`--force` shell-out)\nshould be made exhaustive and the safe-HEAD-move logic consolidated into ONE\nguarded choke-point (capture expected HEAD, refuse-or-replay committed-ahead,\nreflog+oplog) that all callers route through, so a fifth path can't silently\nreintroduce it. Remaining audited movers judged SAFE: merge.rs default-ws\nbranch reattach (branch ref protects commits) and recover.rs populate_from_snapshot\n(target IS the recovered work) — but verify these get the same choke-point.\n","kind":"bug","title":"maw ws advance ORPHANS committed-ahead work and reports success — fourth unguarded HEAD-mover (same class as bn-3d4a/bn-29z8/bn-20sa)"}	blake3:DL136dvSqsqeJwvZdDLC6sal_r5eHjhgo5giUjQIq0s
1781372477548408	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy2hM		item.comment	bn-8flz	{"body":"GIX CONNECTION (per lead question): these orphaning paths shell out to 'git checkout --detach <epoch>' / '--force' guarded by a STALE TODO(gix) (checks.rs:325, working_copy.rs:339): 'checkout_tree() does not update HEAD, and write_ref(HEAD) doesn't reliably create a detached HEAD in linked worktrees — keep git checkout --detach until gix gains proper worktree HEAD support.' That blocker is RESOLVED: maw-git set_head (checkout_impl.rs) writes the linked-worktree HEAD file atomically (+reflog as of bn-20sa) and checkout_tree updates the worktree natively. PROOF: the rebase path (rebase.rs:855-862) ALREADY moves HEAD+worktree fully natively (set_head + checkout_tree, zero shell-out) on sibling linked worktrees in production. The sync/advance/working_copy paths just never got migrated after set_head matured — copy-pasted TODO never revisited. The 'git checkout --detach <epoch>' shell-out is a BLIND tree-replacer (moves HEAD + overwrites worktree with no maw-awareness of ahead-ness) — that blindness is WHY each call site needs a hand-bolted guard and why this bug (advance) slipped a fourth time. FIX FRAMING: the safety choke-point and the gix migration are the SAME work — replace the scattered checkout shell-outs with ONE native primitive safe_advance_head(ws, target) = committed-ahead check (gix is_ancestor) -> replay-or-refuse -> checkout_tree + set_head + reflog/oplog, and route sync/advance/working_copy through it. Retire the stale TODO."}	blake3:rk6FcJ_Le-jQRWNLxqVG25QJLmiaTBdx75QHaFNVGIg
1781372623884861	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy2xM		item.move	bn-8flz	{"state":"doing"}	blake3:Ahy-F5cOP9OuOYeJV5Md7UW3m4ehER7WQcvB6rwL-7o
